metadata.name: caixes üîä #4
metadata.description:
CLICK TO START
-NOTE: Headphones recomended. Some extreme sounds (frequency and amplitude) can be generated. 


Caixes (boxes):
-8 to 24 rows.
-24 to 48 active boxes in each row (the length of each row is at least the double).
-Full boxes contains one of 8 possible sounds.
-Rows move in two possible directions and have diferent velocities and sizes.
-when two adjacent boxes have the same sound type, are full and diferent directions, the synthesizer for that sound is activated.
-when they are activated, there is a possibility that the two lines that contain the sound boxes, change their position.

Params:

"Show empty boxes": show(true) empty boxes.
"Dark Mode": Dark (true) / light (false) mode.
"Squares/Rects": Squares (true): height of boxes have the same value of width / rects(false) height of boxes fill all the space.
"Squares/Rects": 0 to 1-> thikness of vertical lines.
"Flash intensity": when two rows are swaped, a flash is activated. Intensity of this flash (low, mid, high)
"Frequency Range": Frequency range of sounds. (random, all, low, high)
"Wave shapes": Select unique wave shape for all sounds (sine, sawtooth, square, triangle) or all of them randomly assigned to each sound.

Features:

"cols": number of active boxes (in screen) for each row (24-48)
"rows": number of rows (8-24)
"check_frames": the boxes are checked every check_frames(8-28)
"same_freq": same frequencies for all rows
"ratio_full": ratio of full boxes over total boxes.
"avg_boxes": average boxes/row
"avg_velocity": average velocity,
"fx_prob": probability of sound effects (less is more),
"change_prob": probability of row swap.


-powered by p5js and p5.sound

metadata.name: circle drops - 'the passenger' sketches #160
metadata.description:
-------------------------------------------------
The work will refresh and restart after some time

Mouse-click switches between:
- screen scaled image
- The large image - with finer details
: right-click: save/copy image
A custom created 'soft' pixel 2D/3D engine 
written in vanilla JavaScript
some more info in the source-code
-------------------------------------------------

From a young age, 
I was exploring the fields around my parents house.

In the early spring. 
after the winter rains; 
and before the farmers would plant new crops.

Looking for fossils, 
old broken pottery with nice designs 
and stone artefacts.

One day I found a Neanderthal stone-axe, 
estimated like 70.000 years old,
wondered about the person that created it, 
how they lived and loved.

-------------------------------------------------

And I imagined like walking in a field or desert 
littered with sand and stones,
and having like an army of little robots 
slightly rearranging the area around me

-------------------------------------------------

For me Art 
is like a language

you can tell a story
create your own alphabet

Imagine, 

if aliens looked at your work,
or someone that lived 100.000 years ago

could it sparkle some magic
and feelings in their brain and soul?

would they like it? Need to understand it?

-------------------------------------------------

xxx amsterdam chillout

August 6, 2022

metadata.name: 0RAL B1NARY: ‚ÄúBINARY ODE‚Äù #257
metadata.description:
An ‚Äúalgorhythmic‚Äù exploration of the oral/aural tradition in poetry. 

‚ÄúZero is a time of night.
Zero is the color of snow.
Zero is the space between notes.
Zero is the silence between words.
Zero is the pause before breath.
Zero is void in the heart of a crowd.
Zero is not nothing, but it‚Äôs not everything.
One is a time of day.
One is the color of spring grass in sunlight.
One is the warmth at the back of my neck when I turn to find you standing there.
One is the rhythm at the base of my spine.
One is the peace at the core of my being.
One is the sound of your voice in the dark.
And one more thing:
Without one I am nothing‚Ä¶‚Äù
‚ÄìTechnelegy 
 

Fusing AI-powered verse, spoken word, original music and visuals all in generative composition, this playful ode to our universal language is inspired by Stiles‚Äô binary-based art and Stern‚Äôs performative poetics. The experiment centers on a transhuman poem by Stiles‚Äô AI alter ego, Technelegy, voiced as zeroes and ones, layered with human- and machine-generated sound ‚Äì evoking ancient data transmissions in the oral tradition as well as the immersive potential of multisensorial, multimedia, metaversal language and literature. Brought into existence via the blockchain, it is a new form of ‚Äútoken word poetry.‚Äù


As with the duo‚Äôs other poetry ‚Äúunreadings,‚Äù all minters will receive an airdropped broadside of the full poem after all editions are collected. A 1/1 media-rich version of the entire poem will also be made available. 
 
Poetic traits:
- 321 editions performed by the algorithm, out of billions of possible combinations
- Each unique piece contains between 3 and 6 (out of 60) lines of generative text from a poem by Technelegy ‚Äì a custom text generator fine-tuned on Stiles‚Äô writing and research material, seeded with prompts from Stiles‚Äô and Stern‚Äôs work ‚Äì translated into binary and performed by Stiles
- 24 possible binary backbeats performed by Stern in his ‚ÄúNathaniel Fun Time‚Äù (NFT) stylings, and generatively re-mixed
- 98 possible intros
- 15 musical stems composed by Kris Bones, generating millions of possible mixes
- Thousands of possible ending combinations 
- 5 fonts, layered in billions of potential ways, including Stern and Stiles‚Äô custom AI font, NNFT (Neural Network Font Type), developed for their ongoing collaboration, ‚ÄúMother Computer‚Äù
- 13 color palettes based on Stern and Stiles‚Äô respective artworka
- Very rare attributes including music-less performance, poem-less music, repeated ‚ÄúB1nary 0de‚Äù (title only)

Click to start and stop or replay. Although the first play through will be the same every time, starting and stopping may create minor variations in your mix (though not any of the core attributes).

0RAL B1NARY: ‚ÄúBINARY ODE‚Äù was produced with partial support from Refraction DAO‚Äôs Creative Grants program, and premiered as part of Refraction Festival at Art Basel Miami 2022. 15% of primary sales go to Refraction, and 5% of primary sales will be donated to Black Girls Code.

metadata.name: Clerestory #299
metadata.description:
Windows welcome daylight, admit fresh air, and offer a view into the outside world. They rarely shatter, always confess the passage of time, and sometimes allow others a chance to look in.

What would the space you're in feel like if it had no windows?

'Clerestory' is an abstract exploration of stained glass windows, drafting shattered sketches for ten potential locations from various perspectives and moments in time. 

Made with WebGL, p5.js, and <3 | CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Minimalist #25
metadata.description:
This abstract art is produced by exercising concepts of minimalism. Each artwork is composed of simple figures and simple engaging colors. 

Each abstract art piece is generated to connect with a specific type of person. When the viewer sees an abstract image that resonates with him or her a connection is made. 

This artwork was produced using computer graphics software and randomly layerd images.

metadata.name: Type-o-Graphic #62
metadata.description:
Type-o-Graphic embraces the ethos of David Carson's groundbreaking graphic design work. It explores the intersections of typography, design, art and chance, harnessing the power of randomness to create a series of posters that are a frenetic celebration of typographic chaos.

This collection is intended to be customized and printed. Your initial thumbnail output is only the beginning ‚Äî several parameters are changeable to find a combination and format to your liking. Please use the keys below to explore the thousands of possible variations within each piece.

Features:
B - Toggle border
N - Change border colour
K - Change background colour (if visible)
T - Toggle top finish (if applicable)
Up/Down - Change colour palette (43)
Left/Right - Change blend modes (20)
L - Change to Landscape
P - Change to Portrait
S - Save image

0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 - Change resolution of image
0 - 600 x 900 - (low-res)
1 - 1200 x 1800 - 4x6" @ 300dpi - (default)
2 - 2400 x 3600 - 8x12" @ 300dpi
3 - 3600 x 5400 ‚Äì 12x18" @ 300dpi
4 - 4800 x 7200 - 16x24" @ 300dpi
5 - 7200 x 10800 - 24x36" @ 300dpi

See accompanying article for more info:
https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/type-o-graphic

Created with p5js by fauxjebus in 2023
Follow me on twitter or instagram @fauxjebus

metadata.name: CENTURY-XXX-METAFRANKE #260
metadata.description:
1 of 5 in CENTURY-XXX, Series 2
Edition of 1000

Tribute to Herbert W. Franke
‚ÄúIn Honor of the Dinosaur of Computer Art‚Äù 

Herbert W. Franke, a pioneer of computer art, passed away on July 16, 2022 at the age of 95. CENTURY-XXX-METAFRANKE is an homage to Franke‚Äôs MONDRIAN software developed for the Texas Instruments TI 99/4 home computer in 1979, and it‚Äôs a fundraiser to digitize his archive:

‚ÄúOur goal is to raise 20,000 Euro so that ZKM Karlsruhe can digitize Herbert W. Franke‚Äôs 1,800 manuscripts and make them publicly available. If we raise more money, it will be donated to the R√ºtgers Foundation which supports children and young adults in Africa so that they can get access to and work with technology.‚Äù 

Each frame, a single ‚Äúpixel‚Äù is added to the CENTURY-XXX-METAFRANKE image. When the software first loads, 100,000 frames are run in the background to start things off. Keep it running for hours or days to see it transform entirely ‚Äî it‚Äôs an ‚Äúinfinite animation.‚Äù

metadata.name: Bloc.Plan #39
metadata.description:
Working as an architect and interior designer daily, I always find that creating space is something interesting. Especially a block plan. As an architectural drawing, it serves to inform the viewer of the presence or absence of a space by composing positive and negative spaces on the site. Through this, I found out that block plan can be a captivating visual art as well.

Press [s] to save captured image
